wadd a salaryadd benefitsadd an interview connect with utah retirement systemsconnect with utah retirement systems on facebookconnect with utah retirement systems on linkedin follow utah retirement systemsfacebook more tweets for utah retirement systems » latest news utah retirement systems  wikipedia utah retirement systems from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search utah retirement systems agency overview formed  headquarters  east  south salt lake city utah agency executive dan andersen executive director website  utah retirement systems administers pension plans and retirement savings plans for public employees in the state of utah there are eight separate definedbenefit pension plans administered by urs as well as various retirement savings plans as of december   the urs was managing over  billion in its pension trust funds for nearly  members besides the pension trust funds the urs manages a k b a traditional ira and roth ira with around  billion in assets combined at the end of  contents  membership  governanace  history  references  external links membershipedit members of the eight urs pension systems are the employees of over  different employers the two largest systems are the public employees noncontributory retirement systems tier i and tier ii with  participating employers including all of utahs school districts the state of utah and its counties and various political subdivisions the old contributory system has  employers the public safety system has  and the firefighters system has  employers tier  public safety and firefighters has  there is a separate retirement system for judges and one for governors and legislators  employers participate in the urs  savings plans and  in the k plans governanaceedit urs is run by a sevenmember board whose members are appointed by the governor four of the members represent the investment community one represents the teachers and one represents state employees the state treasurer is an exofficio member of the retirement board the board appoints the executive director in addition to the retirement board there is an advisory membership council made up of representatives from the member employee groups historyedit many public employees in utah had some kind of pension before the creation of the urs in  as early as  there was a statewide retirement system for firefighters many cities had a retirement system for their police in the s in  prison guards got a retirement system all of these would eventually be absorbed into ursadministered systems in  the utah education association drew up a plan for a retirement system for teachers this became the basis for the teachers retirement system which went into effect in  covering both teachers and administrators the state officers and employees retirement system of utah later named the public employees retirement system was created in  also optional state coverage was established for judges and local government employees in  joint administration was established for public employees and teachers systems the school employees system public employees system judges system public safety system including highway patrol prison guards system former employee retirement system and firefighters system were placed under a single board the public employees and teachers employees systems were consolidated into the state retirement system this was the creation of the urs later in the s utah firefighters system and judges system were added also the utah legislature established a subcommittee on retirement in the s custody of the retirement funds was transferred to the retirement board from the state treasurer and the retirement system became an independent agency the retirement board was restructured altering the board membership and establishing a membership council a system for judges was added in the s in  the utah legislature created a tier ii retirement plan for new employees with a smaller benefit than the old plan the motivation was to avoid the pension problems that have affected or threatened to affect many other jurisdictions people hired after july   choose either a traditional pension plan or a ktype plan with the state contributing  percent of an employee’s salary  percent for uniformed workers to whichever plan a worker chooses employer contributions to the pension plan for new employees are capped at  of the employees salary the tier ii plans require  more years of employment for eligibility the legislature also limited postretirement reemployment referencesedit  urs  comprehensive annual financial report p   utah retirement systems returns  in  outpacing its benchmark pensions and investments may    urs  comprehensive annual financial report p   urs  comprehensive annual financial report p   a b c d about utah retirement systems  history on urs website  httpswwwursorgmangopdfursmiscellaneousminihistorypdf  under tier i employees are elligible to receive  of their salary per year of employment eg retirement after  years earns a pension thats  of their salary under tier ii employees earn  of their salary per year of employment  pension funds strained states look at k plans new york times february    stressed states are forcing workers to retire later wall street journal aug    state workers rally against bills to change retirement benefits the salt lake tribune february   external linksedit urs website retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitleutahretirementsystemsoldid categories government of utahretirementpublic pension funds in the united stateshidden categories articles created via the article wizard navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload f